       "  'body': 'Three changes: two flaky/infra CI fixes and a stale-xfail cleanup the first one surfaces. All unrelated to feature work.\\n\\n### 1. Minimum Versions worker segfault\\n\\nThe `minimum-versions` pixi environment uses `solve-strategy = \"lowest-direct\"`, which resolved `python = \"3.11.*\"` to the absolute floor — **3.11.0**. Under `PYTHONDEVMODE=1`, pytest formats the traceback of unraisable exceptions, and CPython 3.11.0 segfaults doing so via a frame-teardown bug (python/cpython#99729, fixed in 3.11.1), crashing test workers intermittently (`[gw2] node down`). Floor the env to `python >=3.11.1`. The lock update is targeted (`pixi update -e minimum-versions python`): only the min-versions Python moves 3.11.0 → 3.11.1; all other environments and the minimum dependency floors (numpy 1.26.0, pyarrow 13.0.0, …) are unchanged.\\n\\n### 2. Stale fastparquet xfail (surfaced by #1)\\n\\nMoving min-versions to 3.11.1 flips `test_read_filters[fastparquet]` from fail → pass (it was only ever satisfied on 3.11.0), so the `strict` xfail reported an unexpected pass. The marker is removed.\\n\\n### 3. pyodide wheel build cleanup failure\\n\\nThe `cp312-pyodide_wasm32` wheel build (and the nightly wheel builds on `main`) fail after a successful build+test: pytest\\'s cacheprovider writes a `pytest-cache-files-*` dir into `site-packages/pandas/` with permissions the host runner can\\'t traverse under emscripten, so cibuildwheel\\'s post-test `shutil.rmtree` dies with `PermissionError`. Disable the cache for the pyodide test run (`-p no:cacheprovider`) so the dir is never created.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)',\n",
