       "  'body': '### Pandas version checks\\n\\n- [x] I have checked that this issue has not already been reported.\\n\\n- [x] I have confirmed this bug exists on the [latest version](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/whatsnew/index.html) of pandas.\\n\\n- [ ] I have confirmed this bug exists on the [main branch](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/dev/getting_started/install.html#installing-the-development-version-of-pandas) of pandas.\\n\\n\\n### Reproducible Example\\n\\n```python\\n# Python version\\nimport pandas as pd\\ns = pd.Series([\"a\", \"b\", \"a\", pd.NA], dtype=\"category\")\\ns == \"a\"\\n# s != \"a\" # similar\\n```\\n\\n```r\\n# R version\\ns <- factor(c(\"a\", \"b\", \"a\", NA))\\ns == \"a\"\\n# s != \"a\"\\n```\\n\\n### Issue Description\\n\\nFollowing doc, the pandas.Categorical represent a categorical variable in classic R / S-plus fashion.\\n\\nHowever comparison to missingness (== or !=) is handled differently.\\n\\n```\\n# python\\n>>> s = pd.Series([\"a\", \"b\", \"a\", pd.NA], dtype=\"category\")\\n... s == \"a\"\\n\\n0     True\\n1    False\\n2     True\\n3    False\\ndtype: bool\\n\\n# r\\n> s <- factor(c(\"a\", \"b\", \"a\", NA))\\n> s == \"a\"\\n[1]  TRUE FALSE  TRUE    NA\\n```\\n\\n### Expected Behavior\\n\\nIn the chunk above last element of pd.Series is False, where should be pd.NA for consistency (with R and intuition/logic)\\n\\nIf possible, I\\'d suggest to make this consistent to R (both for newcomers and to avoid boilerplate code after comparison of any categorical). Otherwise I\\'d suggest to notice this in: \\n\\nhttps://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/user_guide/categorical.html#differences-to-r-s-factor\\n\\nMany thanks as always, best\\n\\n### Installed Versions\\n\\n<details>\\n\\nINSTALLED VERSIONS\\n------------------\\ncommit                : 9c8bc3e55188c8aff37207a74f1dd144980b8874\\npython                : 3.14.3\\npython-bits           : 64\\nOS                    : Linux\\nOS-release            : 6.12.86+deb13-amd64\\nVersion               : #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Debian 6.12.86-1 (2026-05-08)\\nmachine               : x86_64\\nprocessor             : \\nbyteorder             : little\\nLC_ALL                : None\\nLANG                  : it_IT.UTF-8\\nLOCALE                : it_IT.UTF-8\\n\\npandas                : 2.3.3\\nnumpy                 : 2.4.6\\npytz                  : 2026.2\\ndateutil              : 2.9.0.post0\\npip                   : None\\nCython                : None\\nsphinx                : None\\nIPython               : 9.14.1\\nadbc-driver-postgresql: None\\nadbc-driver-sqlite    : None\\nbs4                   : 4.15.0\\nblosc                 : None\\nbottleneck            : None\\ndataframe-api-compat  : None\\nfastparquet           : None\\nfsspec                : None\\nhtml5lib              : None\\nhypothesis            : None\\ngcsfs                 : None\\njinja2                : 3.1.6\\nlxml.etree            : None\\nmatplotlib            : 3.11.0\\nnumba                 : None\\nnumexpr               : None\\nodfpy                 : None\\nopenpyxl              : 3.1.5\\npandas_gbq            : None\\npsycopg2              : None\\npymysql               : None\\npyarrow               : 24.0.0\\npyreadstat            : None\\npytest                : None\\npython-calamine       : None\\npyxlsb                : None\\ns3fs                  : None\\nscipy                 : 1.17.1\\nsqlalchemy            : None\\ntables                : None\\ntabulate              : 0.10.0\\nxarray                : None\\nxlrd                  : None\\nxlsxwriter            : None\\nzstandard             : None\\ntzdata                : 2026.2\\nqtpy                  : None\\npyqt5                 : None\\n\\n</details>\\n',\n",
