       "  'body': \"closes #8560\\n\\n`DataFrame.query` now raises `ValueError` when the expression does not evaluate to a boolean result, instead of silently passing the non-boolean result through to `.loc`/`__getitem__`, where it gets misinterpreted as a row indexer. For example, `df.query('cat')` on an integer column previously returned nonsense rather than erroring.\\n\\nBoolean masks continue to work, including nullable/pyarrow boolean ExtensionArrays and 2-D boolean DataFrame masks (e.g. `df.query('(@a>0) & (@b>0)')`).\\n\\nPicks up the approach from the stale GH-46862, incorporating the EA / 2-D-mask review feedback raised there.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\n",
