       "   'merged_at': None},\n",
       "  'body': 'closes #57587\\n\\n`df.plot` on a `PeriodIndex` rendered different x-axis tick labels for equivalent frequencies such as `\"h\"` vs `\"60min\"`. The line-position symptom was fixed in GH-58322 and the tick-spacing symptom in GH-64376, but no test guarded that equivalent frequencies produce identical tick labels — so a regression of the more visible symptom would have gone unnoticed.\\n\\nThis adds a regression test (`test_finder_period_equivalent_freq_same_labels`) asserting that equivalent freq pairs (`h`/`60min`, `2h`/`120min`, `D`/`24h`) render the same major+minor tick labels. Confirmed it fails when the GH-64376 fix is reverted.\\n\\nTest-only; no whatsnew (the user-visible fix already has entries from GH-58322 / GH-64376).',\n",
