       "   'merged_at': None},\n",
       "  'body': 'closes #16147\\n\\nThe primary repro in GH-16147 (`mi.set_levels([], level=\"a\")`, scalar level) was already fixed by GH-48643, which guarded the scalar-`level` branch of `_require_listlike` against an empty outer sequence. That fix left the parallel `level is None or is_list_like(level)` branch unguarded, so an empty outer sequence still indexed `arr[0]` and raised `IndexError: list index out of range`:\\n\\n```python\\nmi = pd.MultiIndex(levels=[[], []], codes=[[], []], names=[\"a\", \"b\"])\\nmi.set_levels([], level=None)    # IndexError\\nmi.set_levels([], level=[\"a\"])   # IndexError\\nmi.set_codes([], level=None)     # IndexError (same helper)\\n```\\n\\nThis mirrors the existing `len(arr) > 0 and` guard onto that branch, so the empty outer sequence now falls through to the existing length validation in `_set_levels` and raises a clear `ValueError` (`\"Must set non-zero number of levels.\"` / `\"Length of codes must match ...\"`). Genuinely malformed non-empty input still raises `TypeError` as before.',\n",
