       "   'merged_at': None},\n",
       "  'body': 'closes #65903\\ncloses #65904\\ncloses #65905\\n\\nHardens the C-level JSON serialization helpers against NULL returns and a use-after-free:\\n\\n- `int64ToIso` (`date_conversions.c`): when `make_iso_8601_datetime` fails, `result` was freed but execution fell through to `strlen(result)` / `return result` — a use-after-free. Added the missing `return NULL;`, matching the existing pattern in the sibling `int64ToIsoDuration` (GH-65903).\\n- `get_long_attr` (`objToJSON.c`): NULL-check `PyObject_GetAttrString` before dereferencing, consistent with the existing `_creso` error handling in the same function (GH-65904).\\n- `total_seconds` (`objToJSON.c`): NULL-check `PyObject_CallMethod` and switch the unsafe `PyFloat_AS_DOUBLE` macro to the safe `PyFloat_AsDouble` (GH-65905).\\n\\nAll three code paths are guarded upstream by type checks (`PyObject_HasAttrString(..., \"_value\")` / `PyDelta_Check`), so I couldn\\'t construct an input that actually triggers a crash on `main` — these are defensive hardening fixes, hence no regression test.\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)',\n",
