       "  'body': 'closes #18356\\n\\nThe reshaping user guide claimed that *both* `stack` and `unstack` \"implicitly sort the index levels involved\". Since the new `stack` implementation (default in 3.0) preserves the order of the stacked column level and never sorts, this was inaccurate.\\n\\n`unstack` still sorts (both the level it moves to columns and the remaining row index), so the round-trip example just below still produces a sorted copy — the wording is updated to attribute that sorting to `unstack` alone.\\n\\nThe original inconsistency reported in GH-18356 (flat columns not sorted while `MultiIndex` columns were) is resolved by the new `stack`: neither sorts now.',\n",
