       "  'body': 'closes #42907\\n\\nClarifies how `func` is applied by `DataFrameGroupBy.transform` / `SeriesGroupBy.transform`:\\n\\n- The `DataFrameGroupBy.transform` summary now states that a UDF operates on each column of each group separately (each column passed as a `Series`), which GH-42907 reported was unclear.\\n- Fixed the leftover `f` parameter name in the Notes section of both docstrings — the parameter is `func`.\\n- Reworded the *\"if this is a DataFrame, f must support application column-by-column\"* bullet, which was vacuous in the `DataFrameGroupBy` docstring (the group is always a DataFrame there) and irrelevant in the `SeriesGroupBy` docstring (a Series group has no columns).\\n\\nDoc-only change. Doctests for both methods pass (10 + 6, no failures).\\n\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)',\n",
