       "  'body': 'closes #41628\\n\\n`merge_asof`\\'s `left_on`/`right_on` already accept an array-like vector (treated as a synthetic join column), matching `merge` and `merge_ordered`, but the docstring only documented `label`. This updates the parameter descriptions to reflect the array-like support.\\n\\nNote that unlike `merge_ordered`, `merge_asof` only permits a *single* asof key — passing more than one key raises `MergeError: can only asof on a key` — so the wording follows `merge`\\'s singular \"array ... treated as if it were a column\" phrasing rather than `merge_ordered`\\'s \"vector or list of vectors\".\\n\\nThe behavior is already covered by tests (the `GH-42844` test in `test_merge_asof.py` passes a `date_range` vector as `left_on`/`right_on`), so this is doc-only.\\n',\n",
