       "  'body': \"closes #64825\\n\\n`concat` with `keys`/`levels` (or with concatenated objects whose index is) an overlapping :class:`IntervalIndex` raised ``InvalidIndexError: cannot handle overlapping indices``. An overlapping ``IntervalIndex`` is not unique-as-index, so the bare ``get_indexer`` call in ``_make_concat_multiindex`` raised — even though the interval values are distinct.\\n\\nSwitch the two relevant lookups to ``Index.get_indexer_for``, which dispatches to ``get_indexer_non_unique`` for non-unique indexes. This fixes both the ``keys``/``levels`` path (the one in the traceback) and a second, previously-unreported spot on the concatenated objects' own index.\\n\\nSupersedes the stale GH-64835 and GH-64843.\",\n",
