       "  'body': 'closes #39705\\n\\nPlotting an empty subset of a `DatetimeIndex`/`PeriodIndex`-indexed object onto an *existing* time-series axis raised, whereas the regular-index case (GH-39705 \"case 1\") just adds an empty line with no error.\\n\\n`use_dynamic_x` assumed a non-empty index. With an empty index it failed two ways:\\n- sub-daily freq (e.g. `\"10s\"`) → `IndexError` at `Period(index[0], freq_str)`\\n- daily-or-coarser freq (e.g. `\"D\"`, `\"ME\"`) → `ValueError` later in `get_xlim` (the daily branch `index[:1].is_normalized` returns `True` for an empty index, routing zero-size data into the ts path)\\n\\nFix: return `False` for an empty index so it routes through the regular (non-dynamic-x) path that the regular-index case already uses — an empty line is added, no error.\\n\\nAdded a parametrized regression test (`10s`/`D`/`ME`).',\n",
