       "   'merged_at': None},\n",
       "  'body': 'closes #48122\\n\\nThe hand-written ISO 8601 duration parser used by the ``Timedelta`` constructor capped hour and minute components at two digits, so ``Timedelta(\"PT100M\")`` and ``Timedelta(\"PT100H\")`` raised ``ValueError`` while ``Timedelta(\"PT99M\")`` / ``Timedelta(\"PT99H\")`` parsed fine.\\n\\nThe cap was inconsistent with the parser\\'s own handling of the seconds/weeks/days components (which have no digit-count limit — e.g. ``PT300S`` already worked), and inconsistent with ISO 8601, which places no digit-count restriction on duration components. It also wasn\\'t a clock-range check: out-of-range values like ``P1DT25H61M61S`` were already accepted. This PR removes the check.\\n\\n- [x] closes #48122\\n- [x] Tests added and passed\\n- [x] All code checks passed\\n- [x] Added an entry in the relevant `doc/source/whatsnew/vX.X.X.rst` file',\n",
